               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#ai-catalogue">
                     <p>الزهر المنثور على شرح الصدور في احوال الموتى والقبور</p>
                     <p>Az-Zahru'l-Manthúr, a commentary by 'Abdu's-Salám ibn Ibráhim al-Laqání <lb/>
                                on as-Suyuti's work on the state of the Dead in their tombs, entitled Sharhu's- <lb/>
                                Sudúr fí Ahwáli'l-Mawtà wa'l-Qubúr. For the text and its author (d. 911/1505) <lb/>
                                see Brockelmann, vol. II, p. 146, No. 30; and for the commentator, who died <lb/>
                                1078/1668, ibid., p. 307.
                            </p>
                     <p>After the Bismilláh the commentary begins quite abruptly:</p>
                     <p>جبر الخ <lb/>
                                قوله ابو نعيم اسمه احمد بن عبد الله قوله مجاهد بن جبر
                            </p>
                     <p>This commentary might be a help to understanding the text, but is of little value or interest without it.</p>
                  </summary>
